    <div id="mgnavsub"><ul id="mgnavsubl"><li><a href="/en/3/">Mageia&nbsp;3 </a></li><li><a href="/en/downloads/">Download </a></li><li><a href="/en/for-pc/">For PC </a></li><li><a href="/en/for-server/" class="sel">For server </a></li></ul></div>    <div class="para" style="width: 600px;">
        <section>
            <p>Mageia 3 has all the main services and server packages you will need to run your server. </p><p>Aside from the cross-section included here, you will find many others in the repositories: you can use rpmdrake to search for packages, or check the <a href="http://mageia.madb.org">Mageia App DB</a>. </p><h3>Administration </h3><p>For centralised administration, we include puppet 2.7.21; we use it widely in <a href="//svnweb.mageia.org/adm/puppet/">our own infrastructure</a>. </p><p>The entire High Availability stack has been updated, and now includes drbd 8.4.2, Corosync 2.3.0 and Pacemaker 1.1.8. </p><h3>Databases </h3><p>Databases included are PostgreSQL 8.4.17; MariaDB 5.5.28, which replaces MySQL; BDB. </p><p>And there are NoSQL servers too: CouchDB 1.2.1, Redis 2.6.5, MongoDB 2.2.2. </p><h3>Servers </h3><p>Web servers include Apache 2.4.4, Cherokee 1.2.101 and lighttpd 1.4.32. </p><p>For file and directory sharing and network printing on heterogeneous networks, we have Samba 3.6.15, OpenLDAP 2.4.33 and Cups 1.5.4. </p><p>Mail servers included with Mageia 3 are Postfix 2.9.6, Cyrus-imapd 2.4.17 and Dovecot 2.1.15. </p>        </section>
    </div>
    <div class="para">
        <p>For more information about these and other packages, check the <a href="https://wiki.mageia.org/en/Mageia_3_Release_Notes">Mageia 3 Release notes</a>. </p><p>You can take a look at the <a href="http://mageia.madb.org/">Mageia Application Database</a> to get a more complete list of Mageia packages. </p>    </div>
